#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/assigning_a_material.rst:85
msgid "Reusing Existing Materials"
msgstr "重用已存在材质"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/assigning_a_material.rst:87
msgid ""
"Blender is built to allow you to reuse *anything*, including material "
"settings, between many objects. Instead of creating duplicate materials, "
"you can simply reuse an existing material. There are several ways to do "
"this using the Materials data-block menu:"
msgstr "Blender原生支持重用 *一切* ，包括物体之间共用材质设置。用户可以直接重用已存在材质，而无需新建材质副本。材质数据块菜单提供了以下几种方法："

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/assigning_a_material.rst:92
msgid ""
"*Single Object* -- With the object selected, click the sphere located to "
"the left of the Material name. A pop-up appears showing all the materials"
" available in the current blend-file. To use one, just click on it."
msgstr "*单个物体* -- 选择物体， 单击材质名称左侧的球形图标， 弹出的菜单会显示当前文件中所有可用材质，单击即可选择。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/assigning_a_material.rst:98
msgid "Select an existing material."
msgstr "选择已存在材质."

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/assigning_a_material.rst:100
msgid "Searching for Materials"
msgstr "搜索材质"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/assigning_a_material.rst:102
msgid ""
"The search field at the bottom of the material list allows you to search "
"the names in the list. For example, by entering \"wood\" all existent "
"materials are filtered so that only materials containing \"wood\" are "
"displayed in the list."
msgstr "使用材质列表底部的搜索框用于搜索列表中的材质名称。例如，输入 \"wood\" 会过滤所有材质，仅显示名称包含 \"wood\" 的材质。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/assigning_a_material.rst:106
msgid ""
"*Multiple Objects* -- In the 3D View, with :kbd:`Ctrl-L` you can quickly "
"link all selected objects to the material (and other aspects) of the "
":ref:`active object <object-active>`. Very useful if you need to set a "
"large number of objects to the same material; just select all of them, "
"then the object that has the desired material, and :kbd:`Ctrl-L` links "
"them to that \"parent\". (See Tip on Linking Data in Creating about data "
"linking)."
msgstr ""
"*多物体* -- 3D视图中，使用 :kbd:`Ctrl-L` ，用户可以快速关联选中物体与 :ref:`活动物体 <object-"
"active>` 的材质(以及其他数据)。这在用户需要为大量物体设置相同材质时非常有用。只需选中所有物体，再选中包含该材质的物体，使用 "
":kbd:`Ctrl-L` 即可关联 \"父物体\" 。 (见数据关联一节关于关联数据的提示)。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/assigning_a_material.rst:116
msgid "Deleting a Material"
msgstr "删除材质"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/assigning_a_material.rst:118
msgid ""
"To delete a material, select the material and click X in the Available "
"Materials List entry."
msgstr "在材质列表选中材质，并单击右侧的 X 按钮，即可删除材质。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/assigning_a_material.rst:120
msgid ""
"Although the material will seem to disappear immediately, the Delete "
"action can depend on how the material is used elsewhere."
msgstr "删除后的材质看似马上消失了，不过删除操作的结果取决于该材质在其他位置是如何使用的。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/assigning_a_material.rst:123
msgid ""
"If the material is linked to the Object and there are other objects which"
" use this material, then the material will be removed from that object "
"(but remain on all its other objects)."
msgstr "如果还有其他物体也在使用与该物体关联的材质，那么从该物体删除材质。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/assigning_a_material.rst:126
msgid ""
"If the \"Fake User\" button (F) has been lit in the Available Materials "
"list, then the material will be retained when the file is saved, even if "
"it has no users."
msgstr "如果可用材质列表的 \"伪用户\" 按钮 (F) 已被点亮，那么即使该材质没有用户，也会在保存文件时保留。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/assigning_a_material.rst:129
msgid ""
"Only if it has 0 \"real\" users, and no \"Fake\" user, will the material "
"be permanently deleted. Note that it will still remain in the Materials "
"list until the blend-file is saved, but will have disappeared when the "
"file is reloaded."
msgstr ""
"当且仅当材质为0 \"真\" 用户，并且没有 “伪” "
"用户时，该材质才会被永久删除。注意在保存文件之前，该材质仍会继续存在于材质列表，但是重新加载该文件后会消失。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/assigning_a_material.rst:137
msgid "Multiple Materials"
msgstr "多材质"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/assigning_a_material.rst:139
msgid ""
"Normally, different colors or patterns on an object are achieved by "
"adding textures to your materials. However, in some applications you can "
"obtain multiple colors on an object by assigning different materials to "
"the individual faces of the object."
msgstr "一般，物体表面的多种颜色和图案是通过给材质添加纹理实现的。不过，有些应用中，用户可以通过给每个面指定不同材质来获得色彩丰富的物体。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/assigning_a_material.rst:148
msgid ""
"To apply several materials to different faces of the same object, you use"
" the Material Slots options in the Materials header panel."
msgstr "用户可以使用材质标题栏面板中的材质槽选项，为同一物体的不同面应用不同材质。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/assigning_a_material.rst:153
msgid "Material menu in edit mode."
msgstr "编辑模式下的材质菜单。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/assigning_a_material.rst:155
msgid ""
"The workflow for applying a second material to some faces of an object "
"covered by a base material is as follows:"
msgstr "为表面已覆盖基础材质的物体的一些面应用其他材质的工作流程如下："

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/assigning_a_material.rst:158
msgid ""
"In Object Mode, apply the base material to the whole object (as shown in "
":doc:`Assigning a material "
"</render/blender_render/materials/assigning_a_material>`)."
msgstr ""
"物体模式下， 对整个物体应用基础材质 (步骤如 :doc:`指定材质 "
"</render/blender_render/materials/assigning_a_material>`)。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/assigning_a_material.rst:160
msgid ""
"Create/select the second material (the whole object will change to this "
"new material)."
msgstr "新建/选中第二种材质(整个物体会修改为使用该材质)。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/assigning_a_material.rst:161
msgid "In the Active Material box, re-select the base material."
msgstr "在活动材质盒，重新选择基础材质。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/assigning_a_material.rst:162
msgid ""
"Go to Edit Mode and Face Select (a new box appears above the Active "
"Material box with Assign/Select/Deselect)."
msgstr "进入编辑模式，切换面选择模式(在活动材质盒上方会出现指定/选择/取消选择按钮)。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/assigning_a_material.rst:163
msgid "Select the face/faces to be colored with the second material."
msgstr "选择将赋予第二种材质的面。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/assigning_a_material.rst:164
msgid ""
"In the Object Material Slots box, click the :kbd:`Plus` to create a new "
"slot, and while this is still active, click on the second material in the"
" Available Materials list."
msgstr "在物体材质槽，单击 :kbd:`Plus` 新建材质槽，新建材质槽被激活，在可用材质列表选择新建的第二种材质。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/assigning_a_material.rst:166
msgid ""
"Click the Assign button, and the second material will appear on the "
"selected object faces."
msgstr "单击指定按钮，选中的面修改为第二种材质。"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/assigning_a_material.rst:168
msgid ""
"You can also make this new material a copy of an existing material by "
"adding the data-block:"
msgstr "还可以通过添加数据块，使用已有材质的副本作为新材质:"

#: ../../manual/render/blender_render/materials/assigning_a_material.rst:170
msgid ""
"Select the object, get the material, :kbd:`RMB` and Copy data to "
"clipboard. When you have renamed the material, click \"Link: Data\" to "
"link to the existing material. Proceed to assign faces as required. NB: "
"If you change the material on the original object, the new object color "
"changes too."
msgstr ""
"选择物体，获得材质， :kbd:`RMB` 并复制数据到剪贴板。重命名材质后，单击 \"链接: 数据\" "
"，关联现有材质。按照需求为表面指定材质。注意：如果修改原始物体的材质，新物体的颜色也会随之变化。"

